we can create different kinds of secret.
here we are creating generic

This is an example of an imperative command in kubernetes.
imperative commands are where we run a command to create an actual object.
It does not list out the password. That is why we are using this.
Remember the secrets always when doing this.

kubectl create secret generic jwt-secret --from-literal=JWT_KEY=asdf
kubectl get secrets

